parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including airbag malfunction, brake light failure, and cruise control problems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to fail, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to malfunction or not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The electrical system failures can cause a fire hazard, leading to serious damage or injury.
